Build a Todo list web app as a single self-contained HTML file
(HTML + CSS + JavaScript, no external dependencies or build step).

Requirements:
- An input field and "Add" button to create new todos (also support pressing Enter)
- Each todo can be marked complete (toggles a strikethrough style) and deleted
- Filter buttons: All / Active / Completed
- A counter showing how many active items remain
- Persist todos to localStorage so they survive a page refresh, and re-render
  from storage on load
- Don't allow adding empty or whitespace-only todos
- Clean, responsive layout that works on mobile and desktop

Don't use any frameworks or CDNs — plain vanilla JS. The whole thing should
run by opening the file in a browser.